{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0d01c049-d68b-470b-b3bd-128b0bdfc619","content":"Two things change when moving to xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n**1. Filter syntax changes**\n\nThe VSTest `--filter` syntax (`FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke`) is replaced by the MTP `--filter` syntax, which uses **different operators**:\n\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|---|---|\n| `~` (contains) | `~=` |\n| `=` (equals) | `=` |\n| `&` (and) | `&` |\n| `FullyQualifiedName` | `FullyQualifiedName` |\n| `Category` | `Category` |\n\n**2. The runner flag changes**\n\nWith `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`, you run the test project directly (or via `dotnet test`), but filters are passed with `--filter` using MTP syntax.\n\n**Your new command:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe only syntactic change is `~` → `~=` (the \"contains\" operator in MTP). The `&` (and) and `=` (equals) operators are the same.\n\n**Alternatively**, if you run the test executable directly (MTP-native style):\n\n```bash\ndotnet run -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"94a524e8-65b4-4959-ac96-b859f3416078","outputTokens":344,"requestId":"E83C:1E8CE8:25FC062:287AB77:6A049432"},"id":"b60c8c8e-2d3b-4796-bade-bdecc6ac424e","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:09:49.078Z","parentId":"36bfbc89-6529-4ec6-9509-6c4cfdb8080e"}
